thread.title: Brazil's economy sheds 95,602 jobs in September
thread.title_full: Brazil's economy sheds 95,602 jobs in September | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Brazil's economy sheds 95,602 jobs in September
text:
BRASILIA Oct 23 Brazil's economy shed a net 95,602 payroll jobs in September, the labor ministry said on Friday, as Latin America's largest country heads toward a prolonged recession.
Brazilian companies were expected to have fired a net 65,000 workers in September, according to the median forecast of 12 economists. Brazil lost 86,543 jobs in August. (Reporting by Silvio Cascione ; Editing by Chris Reese )
